The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Ashok Leyland, a Hinduja flagship company, has recorded a 19.2 per cent increase in vehicle sales during May compared with the corresponding period last year. The total number of vehicles sold during May stood at 4,655 units compared with 3,905 units last year, a company release said. A total of 4,332 units were sold in the domestic market during the month while 323 units were exported, the release said. The total production during May also increased to 5,351 units from 3786 units in the year-ago period, it added.

 The Carborundum Universal board has recommended bonus shares to its shareholders in the ratio of 1:1, that is, one share for each one held. The company will utilise Rs 9.33 crore out of the general reserves for allotment of the fully-paid bonus shares, it has informed the BSE.

 Punjab National Bank has introduced current account schemes ? PNB Gaurav and PNB Vaibhav ? aimed at providing concessions and free services to traders at its 1,100 branches under the core banking solution. Under the scheme, the accounts can be opened with an initial deposit of Rs 5,000 only. But, quarterly average balance has to be Rs 1 lakh for the PNB Gaurav current account and Rs 5 lakh for PNB Vaibhav.

 PTC India has inked a 25-year deal with the Madhya Pradesh Electricity Board to sell power from the first phase of its 300-MW Lanco Amarkantak thermal plant. The project is located in Chhattisgarh. The power trading company is also considering signing similar agreements with other projects for a total capacity of nearly 14,000 MW.

 Future Focus Infotech Pvt Ltd is expected to deploy and hire about 450 techies for the top IT companies in India in the next one year. Future Focus has recently been empanelled by the top three IT companies in the country for hiring professionals, mostly in the areas of customer relations management, enterprise resource planning and infrastructure-enabled services segments, for their overseas projects. 

 Cadila Healthcare has received permission to conduct clinical trials on its new molecular entity ? Zyh 1 ? a formula to check cholesterol in blood. The Drug Controller General of India gave its approval to conduct the first phase clinical trials to evaluate the safety profile of drug. The trials will be conducted at Zydus Research Centre.

 Eicher Motors has reported a 33 per cent growth in sales of its commercial vehicles in May. The company sold 1,613 vehicles last month compared with 1,216 in the same period a year ago. The sales growth for the first two months of the current fiscal was 29 per cent. 

